  <summary date="2017-09-29T16:14:40Z" status="Introduced in House">Promoting Good Cyber Hygiene Act of 2017

This bill requires the National Institute of Standards and Technology to establish for the&#160;federal government, the private sector, and any individual or organization a list of best practices to defend against common cybersecurity threats and risks.&#160;

The Department of Homeland Security must&#160;assess cybersecurity threats, the effect of such threats on the federal government's information systems and networks, and submit recommendations for addressing such threats.</summary>
